[
  {
    "id": "page_0282-b001",
    "page_key": 282,
    "order": 1,
    "type": "heading",
    "text": "15.2.1 Analysis of GAN loss function",
    "source": "deepseek+paddle",
    "confidence": "high"
  },
  {
    "id": "page_0282-b002",
    "page_key": 282,
    "order": 2,
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "If we divide the two sums in the first line of equation 15.5 by the numbers I, J of real and generated samples, then the loss function can be written in terms of expectations:",
    "source": "deepseek+paddle",
    "confidence": "high"
  },
  {
    "id": "page_0282-b003",
    "page_key": 282,
    "order": 3,
    "type": "equation",
    "text": "$$\n\\begin{aligned}\nL[\\phi]\n&= -\\frac{1}{J}\\sum_{j=1}^{J}\\log\\left[1-\\mathrm{sig}[f[\\mathbf{x}_{j}^{*},\\phi]]\\right]-\\frac{1}{I}\\sum_{i=1}^{I}\\log\\left[\\mathrm{sig}[f[\\mathbf{x}_{i},\\phi]]\\right] \\\\\n&\\approx -\\mathbb{E}_{\\mathbf{x}^{*}}\\left[\\log\\left[1-\\mathrm{sig}[f[\\mathbf{x}^{*},\\phi]]\\right]\\right]-\\mathbb{E}_{\\mathbf{x}}\\left[\\log\\left[\\mathrm{sig}[f[\\mathbf{x},\\phi]]\\right]\\right] \\\\\n&= -\\int \\Pr[\\mathbf{x}^{*}]\\log\\left[1-\\mathrm{sig}[f[\\mathbf{x}^{*},\\phi]]\\right]d\\mathbf{x}^{*}-\\int \\Pr[\\mathbf{x}]\\log\\left[\\mathrm{sig}[f[\\mathbf{x},\\phi]]\\right]d\\mathbf{x}\n\\end{aligned}\n\\qquad (15.6)\n$$",
    "source": "codex-fusion",
    "confidence": "medium"
  },
  {
    "id": "page_0282-b004",
    "page_key": 282,
    "order": 4,
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "where $\\Pr[\\mathbf{x}^{*}]$ is the probability distribution over the generated samples, and $\\Pr[\\mathbf{x}]$ is the true probability distribution over the real examples.",
    "source": "deepseek+paddle",
    "confidence": "high"
  },
  {
    "id": "page_0282-b005",
    "page_key": 282,
    "order": 5,
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "When $I = J$, the optimal discriminator for an example $\\tilde{\\mathbf{x}}$ of unknown origin is:",
    "source": "deepseek+paddle",
    "confidence": "high"
  },
  {
    "id": "page_0282-b006",
    "page_key": 282,
    "order": 6,
    "type": "equation",
    "text": "$$\n\\Pr[\\mathrm{real}\\mid\\tilde{\\mathbf{x}}]\n= \\mathrm{sig}[f[\\tilde{\\mathbf{x}},\\phi]]\n= \\frac{\\Pr[\\tilde{\\mathbf{x}}\\mid\\mathrm{real}]}{\\Pr[\\tilde{\\mathbf{x}}\\mid\\mathrm{generated}]+\\Pr[\\tilde{\\mathbf{x}}\\mid\\mathrm{real}]}\n= \\frac{\\Pr[\\mathbf{x}]}{\\Pr[\\mathbf{x}^{*}]+\\Pr[\\mathbf{x}]}\n\\qquad (15.7)\n$$",
    "source": "codex-fusion",
    "confidence": "medium"
  },
  {
    "id": "page_0282-b007",
    "page_key": 282,
    "order": 7,
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "where on the right hand side, we evaluate  $\\tilde{x}$  against the generated distribution  $\\Pr[\\mathbf{x}^{*}]$  and the real distribution  $\\Pr[x]$ . Substituting into equation 15.6, we get:",
    "source": "deepseek+paddle",
    "confidence": "high"
  },
  {
    "id": "page_0282-b008",
    "page_key": 282,
    "order": 8,
    "type": "equation",
    "text": "$$\n\\begin{aligned}\nL[\\phi]\n&= -\\int \\Pr[\\mathbf{x}^{*}]\\log\\left[1-\\mathrm{sig}[f[\\mathbf{x}^{*},\\phi]]\\right]d\\mathbf{x}^{*}-\\int \\Pr[\\mathbf{x}]\\log\\left[\\mathrm{sig}[f[\\mathbf{x},\\phi]]\\right]d\\mathbf{x} \\\\\n&= -\\int \\Pr[\\mathbf{x}^{*}]\\log\\left[1-\\frac{\\Pr[\\mathbf{x}]}{\\Pr[\\mathbf{x}^{*}]+\\Pr[\\mathbf{x}]}\\right]d\\mathbf{x}^{*}-\\int \\Pr[\\mathbf{x}]\\log\\left[\\frac{\\Pr[\\mathbf{x}]}{\\Pr[\\mathbf{x}^{*}]+\\Pr[\\mathbf{x}]}\\right]d\\mathbf{x} \\\\\n&= -\\int \\Pr[\\mathbf{x}^{*}]\\log\\left[\\frac{\\Pr[\\mathbf{x}^{*}]}{\\Pr[\\mathbf{x}^{*}]+\\Pr[\\mathbf{x}]}\\right]d\\mathbf{x}^{*}-\\int \\Pr[\\mathbf{x}]\\log\\left[\\frac{\\Pr[\\mathbf{x}]}{\\Pr[\\mathbf{x}^{*}]+\\Pr[\\mathbf{x}]}\\right]d\\mathbf{x}\n\\end{aligned}\n\\qquad (15.8)\n$$",
    "source": "codex-fusion",
    "confidence": "medium"
  },
  {
    "id": "page_0282-b009",
    "page_key": 282,
    "order": 9,
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "Disregarding additive and multiplicative constants, this is the Jensen-Shannon divergence between the synthesized distribution  $\\Pr[x^{*}]$  and the true distribution  $\\Pr[x]$ :",
    "source": "deepseek+paddle",
    "confidence": "high"
  },
  {
    "id": "page_0282-b010",
    "page_key": 282,
    "order": 10,
    "type": "equation",
    "text": "$$\n\\begin{aligned}\nD_{JS}\\left[\\Pr[\\mathbf{x}^{*}]\\Vert\\Pr[\\mathbf{x}]\\right]\n&= \\frac{1}{2}D_{KL}\\left[\\Pr[\\mathbf{x}^{*}]\\Vert\\frac{\\Pr[\\mathbf{x}^{*}]+\\Pr[\\mathbf{x}]}{2}\\right]+\\frac{1}{2}D_{KL}\\left[\\Pr[\\mathbf{x}]\\Vert\\frac{\\Pr[\\mathbf{x}^{*}]+\\Pr[\\mathbf{x}]}{2}\\right] \\\\\n&= \\frac{1}{2}\\int \\Pr[\\mathbf{x}^{*}]\\log\\left[\\frac{2\\Pr[\\mathbf{x}^{*}]}{\\Pr[\\mathbf{x}^{*}]+\\Pr[\\mathbf{x}]}\\right]d\\mathbf{x}^{*}+\\frac{1}{2}\\int \\Pr[\\mathbf{x}]\\log\\left[\\frac{2\\Pr[\\mathbf{x}]}{\\Pr[\\mathbf{x}^{*}]+\\Pr[\\mathbf{x}]}\\right]d\\mathbf{x}\n\\end{aligned}\n\\qquad (15.9)\n$$",
    "source": "codex-fusion",
    "confidence": "medium"
  },
  {
    "id": "page_0282-b011",
    "page_key": 282,
    "order": 11,
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "where $D\\_{KL}[\\bullet\\Vert\\bullet]$ is the Kullback-Leibler divergence.",
    "source": "deepseek+paddle",
    "confidence": "high"
  },
  {
    "id": "page_0282-b012",
    "page_key": 282,
    "order": 12,
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "The first term indicates the distance will be small if, wherever the sample density  $\\Pr[\\mathbf{x}^{*}]$  is high, the mixture  $(\\Pr[\\mathbf{x}^{*}] + \\Pr[\\mathbf{x}])/2$  has high probability. In other words, it penalizes regions with samples  $x^{*}$  but no real examples x; it enforces quality. The second term says that the distance will be small if, wherever the true density  $\\Pr[\\mathbf{x}]$",
    "source": "deepseek+paddle",
    "confidence": "high"
  }
]
